BOARD OF AUDITORS (Wayne) vs. BOARD OF SUPERVISORS (Wayne), No. 16363; 4 D. L. N., 480; 72 N. W., 19.

(Certiorari to Wayne.)

To compel respondent to rescind a resolution providing for a committee' to supervise the work of constructing a county building.

Denied July 16, 1897, on the ground that the act giving to relators the power to supervise the construction of county- buildings, was in conflict with Sec. 9, of Article 10, of the constitution.
